For now here is the CSS version of our map for your enjoyment. We have spent months trying to get the atmosphere and tone of the level to its current state and are now satisfied with it. The map has 64 spawn points, is HDR compatible, and includes a hand-tuned nav ensuring that bots use all the passageways allowed by the layout. We had a lot of fun testing this map both with the team and bots and hope you will have as much fun playing it on your server.
Enjoy.

This map isn't complete 100%, I just wanted to release it to get recommendations, and to see what you all thought of it. The idea first started from wanting to recreate the Pool map from the game S.T.A.L.K.E.R. for CS:S. Then I just kept adding stuff and have what I am offering you now. No real story yet, doesn't really need one anyways. It's just simply an AIM map right now. But, once I'm done with this map, I plan on making a de_ (maybe cs_) version of it as well. Actual Known Problems 1. Men's bathroom near CT Spawn has a section of a wall that I accidently NoDrawed. 2. Ladders/Carved holes are a bitch to get in and out of. Auto To/Do's Lighting is quite...dull...But take this one and hold it up against my first map (seb_deathbox). It looks quite lovely, and much more lively. But still, I'm going to try to tweak the settings to make it look much better. I want to fix those ladders/holes. You can get through them, but sometimes they like to snag you. Some areas of the map don't really make me feel like it's "complete". So I plan on adding more models. Help...Please Aside from telling me that it sucks, I would really like some help for future reference. As I'm a beginner to this and would like to learn as much as possible about this program. I would like to know how to add Place names. I followed the tut found on this site, but it didn't tell me how to add any. Is there any custom models/textures/decal sites out there? Well, thanks for trying my map. Questions? Comments? Email me at sebhael AT hotmail DOT com or just use FPSB's PM system.

Here's my map aim_sealevel. The map takes place in the middle of the Pacific Ocean in a medium sized arena.
Each player gets a Scout at the start of the round and has the opportunity to get one of four AWP on each sides and three HE grenades which are laying right in the center of the map.
The map plays like most aim_ maps and there are enough wooden boxes to take cover at. 

- 32 Players (16CT/16T)
- HDR Ready
- Cubemaps are build
- Bot nav file is included

How to install:

Copy both the .bsp and the .nav into:

"Steam\SteamApps\Username\Counter-Strike Source\cstrike\maps"

I hope you have fun with my map and please leave feedback so I can improve my skills.
</center>

Put aim_sdt_warlock.bsp and aim_sdt_warlock.nav into your maps folder. Inorder for the map to function properly, take sdt.vmf and sdt.vtf and put it into your materials folder. You must add the files in the materials folder to your materials folder.
